<h1>Supervisor Rules and Protocols</h1>

<div class="supervisorContainter">
<h5><span class="underlineBold">EXPECTATIONS AND POLICIES</span></h5>

<p><span class="underlineBold, subsectionTitle">Overall Expectations:</span> Supervisors are expected to handle all situations that arise in the Dow promptly and with professionalism. Supervisors will be the adult presence in the building when the Director/Assistant Director is not at the Dow. You are expected to hold your peers accountable when any Dow Center rules or policies are broken, and are to report those to the Director/Assistant Director via the Supervisor Checklist(comments section). You are expected to go on complete rounds every 30 minutes to ensure the safety of all who are using the Dow. Supervisors are expected to deposit money to the Assistant Director whenever the totals surpass the set amount. Supervisors will be held responsible if the Director/Assistant Director hear of infractions by workers that the supervisor allowed, or did not know happened on their shift. It is your responsibility to be aware of employees who are late or do not show, and to do all you can to solve those problems when they arise, and inform the Director/Assistant Director when that happens so appropriate action can take place. The adult who is "on-call" can be contacted if anything happens that is above your jurisdiction, or that you have questions about.</p>

<p>Supervisors must be OSHA Certified and attend Blood borne Pathogen training at the start of the year.</p>

<p><span class="underlineBold">Supervisor Shirts:</span>: Must be on, visible whenever on duty. If not, a strike will be given.</p>

<p> <div class="underlineBold subsectionTitle"> Your Station(when not on rounds):</div><ul>
    <li> <strong>Sit in tablet chiar in the hallway outside of the weight room.</strong> This allows you to see both sets of doors.</li>
    <li><strong>Do not sit in equipment room, or weight-room</strong></li>
    <li><strong>Do not let visitors hang around or sit in chair.</strong></li></ul></p>

<p><div class="underlineBold subsectionTitle">Homework and Entertainment:</div><ul>
    <li><strong>HOMEWORK/ENTERTAINMENT IS A PRIVILEGE.</strong>You must first and foremost do your job and all that it requires, and expect that all other workers to do so as well. Your homework/entertainment should not distract you when there are students/community members who need your assistance, and for that reason, headphones are <strong>NOT ALLOWED</strong> under any circumstances. You are responsible for holding all other workers accountable for this.</li>
    <li><strnog>Content of material:</strong> (ex: movies, music) You are responsible for monitoring that all movies, music that other workers listen to/watch is appropriate, not offensive to members/children, and at a reasonable volume.</li>
<li><strong>Be proactive:</strong> Look for things to do before you do homework. (Put away volleyball, Wally ball nets, check racquetball courts, locker rooms, other workers)</li>
<li><strong>No headphones while on duty for supervisors or other Dow workers</strong></li>
<li><strong>Look up at doors frequently:</strong> Do not let homeowrk or any activity prevent this.</li>
<li><strong>If privileges become problem or are abused, they will be revoked</strong></li></ul></p>

<h5><span class="underlineBold">DUTIES AND RULES</span></h5>
 <p><div class="underlineBold subsectionTitle">Opening Shift:</div><ul>
     <li>You must arrive 15 minutes before open(6:40am weekdays, 830am Saturday, 1:00pm Sunday) to let yourself and the other employees in the building.</li>
     <li>Within these 15 minutes it is your job to open the building by:<li><ul>
	 <li>Removing the orange bars off all the exits(if maintenance hasn't already)</li>
	 <li>Unlock all of the doors going into the weight-room/track/cardio room</li>
	 <li>Remove all the bars off the back gym doors</li></ul>
       <li>Once everything is open and all the other employees are where they're suppose to be; unlock the front doors</li></ul></p>

<p><div class="underlineBold subsectionTitle">Closing Shift:</div><ul>
    <li>Lock the front doors at 15 minutes till close</li>
    <li>Take the Door Guard book back to the equipment room</li>
    <li>Within the next 15 minutes it's your job to:<ul>
	<li>Make sure things are being picked up in the weight-room and gym</li>
	<li>Make sure all members/students leave by close(12am weekdays, 11pm Saturday/Sunday)<ul>
	    <li>After they leave make sure to put the orange bars on the exit doors they go on</li>
	    <li>Put the bars on the back doors to the gym</li>
	    <li>Shut off and lock up the weight-room sound system</li>
	    <li>Lock up all the dooors into the weight-room, cardio-room, track, classrooms, and dance studios</li></ul></ul>
    <li>Put the Supervisor keys on the hook in the metal box in the office</li><ul>
      <li>Do NOT lock the pad-lock on the outside</li></ul>
    <li>Any completed weight-room or supervisor checklist sheets need to be slipped under the Assistant Director's door while you're leaving</li></ul></p>

<p><div class="underlineBold subsectionTitle">Watching Doors:</div><ul>
    <li><strong>Look up frequently:</strong> watch doors for people sneaking, espically problematic: 11:30am-1:00pm and 5:00pm-8:00pm</li>
    <li><strong>If you catch someone sneaking in:</strong><ul>
	<li>Take name and phone number</li>
	<li>Take name and phone number of member who let them in</li>
	<li>Give information to Brian Morehouse immediately</li>
	<li>Make them pay or leave</li>
	<li>If they refuse to leave they are on private property and you have right to call Campus Safety</li></ul></ul></p>

<p><span class="underlineBold">Supervising Other Workers:</span><ul>
    <li><strong>Demand workers to do jobs correctly:</strong> You are expected to confront workers when not doing their job, but if you feel the need to involve the Director/Assistant Director, do so and they will handle the situation.</li>
    <li><strong>Read their job descriptions:</strong> know how they should be doing their jobs.</li>
    <li><strong>If worker is late or does not show up:</strong><ul>
	<li><span class="underlineBold">Check sub document:</span> Call whoever should be working. If no answer, find sub.</li>
	<li><span class="underlineBold">Write:</span>their name, time, position on supervisor checklist.</li>
	<li><span class="underlineBold">Sit at position:</span> until late person, sub, or next worker arrives.</li></ul>
      <li><strong>When any situations arise with workers(disciplinary, late, no show, etc.):</strong> Write it down on the supervisor checklist, and <strong>  ALSO</strong> <span class="underlineBold"> E-mail Director & Assistant Director </span> to describe the incident/issue that happened. If it is found that there were issues that are NOT reported, the supervisor WILL be held responsible. Supervising your peers is challenging, but no matter if you know the worker or not, you NEED to report it(no protecting your friends)</li></ul></p>

