 <h5><span class="underlineBold">DOW SUPERVISOR EMERGENCY PROTOCOLS</span></h5>

<p>When EMERGENCY SITUATIONS happens at the Dow, we want our supervisors to know with 100% certainty what they're supposed to do. We are incorporating our Dow lifeguards into our emergency action plans, because in many situations (CPR, AED & First Aid certification) they have more emergency training than our superivosrs. See here are your protocols:</p><ul>
  <li>If the person involved in the emergency is CONSCIOUS BUT NEEDS MORE ASSISTANCE THAN YOU CAN GIVE: You must:<li><ol>
      <li>Call Campus Safety Immediately.</li>
      <li>Alert/send someone to get the Dow Lifeguard to come and assist. Campus safety will determine if the ambulance should be called. (use common sense and if you can CLEARLY determine that an ambulance will be needed do not dely in calling them).</li></ol>

    <li>If the person involved is UNCONSCIOUS: You must:</li><ol>
      <li> Call 911 & Campus Safety Immediately</li>
      <li> Alert/send someone to get the Dow Lifeguard to come and assist<br>
	The AED should be present at the scene, and the lifeguard will be the first responder until the ambulance arrives.</li></ol>

  <li>PLEASE DELEGATE TO ANYONE AROUND THE FOLLOWING TASKS:</li><il>
    <li> Getting the AED.</li>
    <li> Calling 911/Campus Safety</li>
    <li> Running to get the lifeguard. You should never leave the patient, so do not feel as though you need to do everything. Anyone around can help with those tasks.</li></ol></ul>

<p> IF THE LIFEGUARD IS CALLED AWAY FROM THE POOL, THE POOL WILL BE TEMPORARILY CLOSED AND MUST BE EVACUATED BY ANYONE USING IT AT THE TIME(with the exception of a supervised Hope swim practice).</p>
